# Branch-aware pre-push parity gate.
#
# Pushes to main run the FULL gate (typecheck + lint + test:run + test:e2e) —
# the same checks GitHub Actions runs on push/PR to main, e2e included — so
# CI failures get caught locally first. Pushes to other branches run a
# scoped gate: full typecheck, lint on changed files only, vitest --changed
# against the diff base. CI still runs the full suite when the branch reaches
# a PR to main.
#
# The full gate's e2e stage needs a dev server; Next 16 allows only one per
# project dir, so the script stops any dev server you have running, runs e2e,
# and ALWAYS restarts it on the same port after — a push never leaves your
# dev server dead.
#
# Explicit skip: `PRE_PUSH_SKIP=1 git push` (logged intent, preferred).
# Emergency bypass: `git push --no-verify` (use sparingly).

bash scripts/pre-push.sh
